-MTZuJUTgslFKJKo7aUO.other-notes: I encountered and spoke to Karen when I saw her sleeping at the bench under the block at 1130pm on 14/2/21. I woke her up and offered her 10 dollars, and asked if she needs any help. She opened up that she has several medical issues and is unable to work. She has been going for cancer treatments at CGH and also some othe rmedical appointments at SGH. From what I spoke to her, I understand that she is a rough sleeper, as i think she has a house in sengkang, but she didnt go into detail as to why she doesnt reside there. She mentioned that she is single so i think she relies on govt/charity support. She shared that she applies for govt help but has to keep reapplying every 3 months and it sometimes isnt enough. More recently with the cancer treatments, she has to eat foods that are a bit more expensive, and she shared she might not have enough money to eat properly on somedays. She also opened up about her negative experiences at charities/FSCs before so i think she is also quite apprehensive about seeking help. I took down her contact and told her i'll try to find out how best I can help her, and give her a call. I hope that homeless hearts of SG can give me a hand as I am quite unsure of how to go about ensuring that she receives the long term support that she needs. Please do feel free to contact me via email/text/call if that is better. Thank you very much.
